At first, I was surprised beyond belief at the generosity of this player and was THAT close to declining. But I realized there was a reason for this gift. <br>
So, I did not decline.<br>
I hit that accept button then /bow and I asked him how can I repay this debt? <br>
His reply was &quot;I give you this armor because of a Promise I made. When I first started, a high ranking player gave me this type of armor and asked me to promise to do the same when I reached 21lvl. Well, you are the recipient of this promise. All I can ask is that in the future, when you reach high level, Promise to help out a new player in this way.&quot;<br>
I was floored by this remark. The roleplaying this fellow showed, the Promise he kept to another player.<br>
Of course, I accepted this Promise. <br>
What person of honor would not accept such a worthy duty. In his honor, I made my fighter type a Paladin.<br>
At this time, I am level 6 and someday I intend to be level 21.<br>
On tha day that I achieve that rank, some new player in the realm of Albion will receive a full suit of Iron boned with the lofty Promise to go with it. <br>
Mayhaps it will be one of you.<br>
Good day and a pleasant tomorrow to you all.<br>
<br>
<br>
Padraigh<br>
aka Heirondal.<br>
